# {{ bakery.project_name }} — frontend (Nuxt 4)

> Generated by [`django-bakery`](https://github.com/Axionore/Django-Barkery). Nuxt 4 · Vue 3.6 · TypeScript 6 · Tailwind v4 · Pinia 3.

The frontend talks to the Django backend via **session cookies**. There is no JWT in localStorage, no token in JS, no Authorization header — Django's `sessionid` cookie (HttpOnly, SameSite=Lax) is the only credential, and Django's `csrftoken` cookie (read by JS) lands in the `X-CSRFToken` header on every mutating request.

## Quickstart

```bash
# From the project root — the pnpm workspace ties frontend + backend.
pnpm install
pnpm --filter frontend dev          # nuxt on http://localhost:{{ bakery.frontend_dev_port }}

# OR via docker compose (preferred — runs Django + Postgres + Mailpit + Nuxt)
docker compose -f compose.local.yml up
```

Nitro's `routeRules` proxy `/api`, `/_allauth`, `/static`, `/media` to Django on `:8000`, so cookies stay first-party and CSRF works without CORS gymnastics.

