## Authentication contract

The SPA talks to `django-allauth`'s **headless** API at `/_allauth/browser/v1/...`. See `apps/users/middleware.py` for the staff-MFA enforcement layer on the backend side.

Login flow (most-common branches — exhaustive Result type in `app/types/allauth.d.ts`):

```
POST /_allauth/browser/v1/auth/login                  { email, password }
  200 → user is signed in ({ data.user })
  401 + flows[].id === "mfa_authenticate" → MFA challenge screen
  401 + flows[].id === "verify_email" → "check your email" screen
  401 (no flows) → invalid credentials
  429 → cool-down screen (allauth's built-in rate limit)
```

### Why session cookies and not JWTs?

Storing tokens in `localStorage` is an OWASP A02 anti-pattern — any XSS becomes total account takeover. With Django's session cookies:
- `sessionid` is `HttpOnly` — XSS cannot read it.
- `SameSite=Lax` blocks cross-site cookie forwarding.
- The CSRF token is the only cookie JS reads, and it's only useful in a same-site context.

If you NEED a JWT (e.g. for a mobile app calling the same API), use [`django-ninja-jwt`](https://django-ninja.dev/guides/authentication/#django-ninja-jwt) (Ninja) or [SimpleJWT](https://django-rest-framework-simplejwt.readthedocs.io/) (DRF) at a separate `/api/token/*` namespace — never mix the two on the same route.

## Calling the typed API

{% if bakery.api_layer == 'ninja' %}
The backend uses **Django Ninja**. The auth model in the generated `apps/api/ninja_api.py` is `django_auth` (session-based) — see [django-ninja auth docs](https://django-ninja.dev/guides/authentication/). From any composable or page:

```ts
const { fetchMe } = useApi();
const me = await fetchMe();   // sessionid cookie forwarded automatically
```

Regenerate the typed schema whenever the backend changes:

```bash
pnpm openapi:gen
```
{% elif bakery.api_layer == 'drf' %}
The backend uses **DRF**. The auth classes are `SessionAuthentication` + `TokenAuthentication` — see [DRF auth docs](https://www.django-rest-framework.org/api-guide/authentication/). The SPA uses SessionAuthentication via the same cookie set by allauth.

```bash
pnpm openapi:gen     # writes app/types/api-schema.d.ts
```
{% else %}
No API layer was selected for this project. Add one in the recipe to get a typed `useApi()` composable.
{% endif %}

## Theming

Tailwind v4 is configured CSS-first in `app/assets/css/main.css` via `@theme`. Brand tokens live there; adjust `--color-brand-*` to your palette. Dark mode is wired via `useColorMode()` (auto-import from `@nuxtjs/tailwindcss` companion); the toggle in the default layout flips between light/dark and persists to `localStorage`.

## Security baseline (what's already on)

- Every fetch uses `credentials: "include"` — required for the session cookie.
- Every mutating fetch sends `X-CSRFToken` via `useCsrf().csrfHeaders()`.
- Strict CSP `connect-src` already includes the Nuxt dev origin (`config/settings/base.py`).
- `vue/no-v-html` ESLint rule bans raw-HTML injection sinks.
- Source maps disabled in production builds (`nuxt.config.ts sourcemap: { server: false, client: false }`).
- Sentry SDK (when `use_sentry=true`) auto-installed; configure `NUXT_PUBLIC_SENTRY_DSN` to enable.

## Bundle-size budget

Default-route initial chunk targets **≤ 350 KB gzipped**. Nuxt's tree-shaking + Tailwind's purge keep us well under that on a clean build.
